"n.恶梦；可怕的事 【英】 n. 恶梦(a terrifying dream) 【记】 组合词：night+mare( 母马，恶魔); 【同】 参考：mare(母马) 【例】 I awoke screaming from a horrible nightmare. n. 恶梦(使人恐惧、害怕和痛苦的梦) 【记】night, mare(n 母马); 晚上的母马－恶梦 【记】night + 音：梦啊 nightmare (n.)  late 13c., ""an evil female spirit afflicting sleepers with a feeling of suffocation,"" compounded from night + mare (3) ""goblin that causes nightmares, incubus."" Meaning shifted mid-16c. from the incubus to the suffocating sensation it causes. Sense of ""any bad dream"" first recorded 1829; that of ""very distressing experience"" is from 1831. Cognate with Middle Dutch nachtmare, German Nachtmahr."
